Frecia: Thank you very much. If or when the time comes, I will ask for that favor.  #line:ch3_p2_FairyForest_25
Frecia: Yes Emma, could you say hello to Rosé when you leave here. It's because of her, isn't it, that you were able to re-enter this forest?  #line:ch3_p2_FairyForest_26

Emma: Ye、 yes… But I'm not sure if I should be the one to go talk to her since she hates me... I feel like I'm irritating her when I talk to her.  #line:ch3_p2_FairyForest_27

Frecia: Well... Emma, that's not true. Rosé may be a little harsh in her language, but she's worried about you. Ever since you were in these woods... and ever since you left the forest she has been always worried. All the time.  #line:ch3_p2_FairyForest_28


Emma: What? Really?  #line:ch3_p2_FairyForest_29

Frecia: Your interest in the outside world and other species made you different from the rest of us in the Fairy Forest. People around you created distance from you, and you closed your mind to our surroundings… Still, wasn't Rosé the only one who talked to you about everything?  #line:ch3_p2_FairyForest_30

Emma: ......  #line:ch3_p2_FairyForest_31

Frecia: Even after you left the forest, Rosé often went outside the fairy forest to check on you, worried that you might come back to this forest or be near this forest. Of course, that would be dangerous, so Rosé herself had to hone her own skills in her own way and get my permission to go out for a very small period of time.  #line:ch3_p2_FairyForest_32
Frecia: It's easy to say, but you have no idea how hard it was for a mere fairy to be allowed to go outside this far, do you Emma?  #line:ch3_p2_FairyForest_33

Emma: ......  #line:ch3_p2_FairyForest_34


Frecia: I'm sure Rosé will be there to see you off when you leave, as she is very responsible. So please speak to her when you do.  #line:ch3_p2_FairyForest_35


Emma: ...Yes. Lady Frecia  #line:ch3_p2_FairyForest_36
